@startuml
title Backend DI Runtime Flow

actor Client
participant "ASP.NET Core\nRouting" as Routing
participant "AdminRecipesController" as Controller
participant "IRecipeService" as IService
participant "RecipeService" as Service
participant "IRecipeRepository" as IRepository
participant "SqliteRecipeRepository" as Repository
database "RecipeDbContext" as DbContext

Client -> Routing: HTTP GET /api/admin/recipes
Routing -> Controller: Resolve controller from DI
note right of Routing
Program.cs has registered:
- AddControllers()
- AddScoped<IRecipeService, RecipeService>()
- AddScoped<IRecipeRepository, SqliteRecipeRepository>()
end note

Controller -> IService: GetAllRecipes(search, category)
IService -> Service: RecipeService instance
Service -> IRepository: GetAll()
IRepository -> Repository: SqliteRecipeRepository instance
Repository -> DbContext: Recipes.ToList()
DbContext --> Repository: Recipe entities
Repository --> Service: Domain recipes
Service --> Controller: RecipeResponse list
Controller --> Routing: Ok(...)
Routing --> Client: HTTP 200 JSON

@enduml
